definitions.definition: A group of people crowded or gathered closely together.
A group of things; a host or swarm.
To crowd into a place, especially to fill it.
To congregate.
To crowd or press, as persons; to oppress or annoy with a crowd of living beings.
Filled with persons or objects; crowded.
Busy; hurried.
(chiefly in combination) Having (a specified number or type of) toes.
definitions.example: He become more pigeon-toed with age.

definitions.definition: Having the end secured by nails driven obliquely; said of a board, plank, or joist serving as a brace, and in general of any part of a frame secured to other parts by diagonal nailing.
To furnish (a stocking, etc.) with a toe.
To touch, tap or kick with the toes.
To touch or reach with the toes; to come fully up to.
To fasten (a piece) by driving a fastener at a near-45-degree angle through the side (of the piece) into the piece to which it is to be fastened.
definitions.example: The framers toed the irregular pieces into the sill.

definitions.definition: To mishit a golf ball with the toe of the club.
A plastic card that has information stored on an embedded computer chip.
The sound of a muffled explosion.
To produce such a sound.
For one's health to decline rapidly (but not as rapidly as crash).
Hard or crusty; dry baked
Crooked; bent.
To wash (something) quickly using water and no soap.
definitions.example: You'd better rinse that stain before putting the shirt in the washing machine.

definitions.definition: To remove soap from (something) using water.
definitions.example: Rinse the dishes after you wash them.

definitions.definition: To thoroughly defeat in an argument, fight or other competition.
The act by which something is rinsed.
definitions.example: The cloth will need frequent rinsings as you wash the car.

definitions.definition: (usually plural) That which is rinsed or washed out.
To schedule again or at a different time.
definitions.example: We'll have to reschedule next Monday's meeting because of the public holiday.

definitions.definition: To reclassify; to change the schedule (division into which something is classified) of.
A preemptive bid.
To appropriate something (before someone else does).
To displace something, or take precedence over something.
To secure (land, etc.) by the right of preemption.
To make a preemptive bid at bridge.
To avoid, especially persistently.
To escape (a threatening evil, an unwelcome task etc).
To screen, hide.
To shove, push.
To give up or relinquish control of, to surrender or to give oneself over, or to yield to one's emotions.
To desist in doing, practicing, following, holding, or adhering to; to turn away from; to permit to lapse; to renounce; to discontinue.
To leave behind; to desert as in a ship or a position, typically in response to overwhelming odds or impending dangers; to forsake, in spite of a duty or responsibility.
definitions.example: Many baby girls have been abandoned on the streets of Beijing.

definitions.definition: To subdue; to take control of.
To cast out; to banish; to expel; to reject.
To no longer exercise a right, title, or interest, especially with no interest of reclaiming it again; to yield; to relinquish.
To surrender to the insurer (an insured item), so as to claim a total loss.
A yielding to natural impulses or inhibitions; freedom from artificial constraint, with loss of appreciation of consequences.
Abandonment; relinquishment.
(British slang) Abandoned children; foundlings.
(British slang) Prostitutes.
To sell again.
A tuk-tuk.
A cycle rickshaw
Any of various compounds of transition metals or of rare earths that exhibit phosphorescence.
Phosphorus.
The act of colliding or crashing.
definitions.example: The skateboarder had a nasty wipeout as she came off the ramp.

definitions.definition: Total destruction or elimination.
definitions.example: The wipeout of this industry could be catastrophic.

definitions.definition: Desire to eat food or consume drink.
Any strong desire; an eagerness or longing.
The desire for some personal gratification, either of the body or of the mind.
Unperfumed; having no scent.
That has not been scented (detected by smell); undetected.
A male domestic chicken (Gallus gallus domesticus) or other gallinaceous bird.
A bird or bat which roosts or is roosting.
An informer.
A violent or disorderly person.
A powerful, prideful, or pompous person.
(originally United States slang) A man.
A wild violet, when used in a children's game based on cockfighting.
Legislation solely devised to benefit the legislators proposing it.
Something homologous; a homologous organ or part, chemical compound or a chromosome.
A word shared by two languages or dialects.
One of a group of similar DNA sequences that share a common ancestry.
A member of a homologous series
